#. (itstool) path: component/summary
#: org.kde.kigo.appdata.xml:10
msgid "Go Board Game"
msgstr "Go Mahai Jokoa"

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.kigo.appdata.xml:12
msgid ""
"Kigo is an open-source implementation of the popular Go game. Go is a "
"strategic board game for two players. It is also known as igo (Japanese), "
"weiqi or wei ch'i (Chinese) or baduk (Korean). Go is noted for being rich in "
"strategic complexity despite its simple rules. The game is played by two "
"players who alternately place black and white stones (playing pieces, now "
"usually made of glass or plastic) on the vacant intersections of a grid of "
"19x19 lines (9x9 or 13x13 for easier games)."
msgstr ""
"Go joko ezagunaren kode irekiko inplementazioa da Kigo. Go taula-joko "
"estrategikoa da bi jokalarientzat. Igo (japoniarra), weiqi edo wei ch'i "
"(txinatarra) edo baduk (korearra) ere  moduan ezagutzen da. Go jokoak nahiz "
"eta arau sinpleak izan konplexutasun estrategiko handia duelako nabarmentzen "
"da. Bi jokalarik jolasten dute, eta txandaka harri zuri eta beltzak jartzen "
"dituzte (joko-piezak, gaur egun beiraz edo plastikoz eginak) 19x19 lerroko "
"sareta bateko bidegurutze hutsetan (9x9 edo 13x13 joko errazagoetarako)."
